#What is Telecom(sort for telecommunication):-
'''
= Telecom means Communication over the distance using technology.

= It involves to transmitting voice, data, text, sound, images, video through the different medium.

= There is two types of medium:-
  1. Wired Network(fiber optic, copper cable)
  2. Wireless Network(mobile network, wi-fi, radio waves, microwave link, satellite)

= Telecom domain is used to connect people over the distance.

= In simple torms, Telecom enables people and systems to connect:-
                                                                  1. Making a phone call
                                                                  2. Sending a text message
                                                                  3. Browsing the internet
                                                                  4. Video calling
'''

#What is the Telecom domain:-
'''
= Telecom domain refers to the industry and the ecosystem.

= When we can built a telecom domain ecosystem, In telecom domain, the design, built, operators,
  and manages communication networks and services.
'''

= Telecom covers multiple functional areas:-
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Area of Domain                          Description
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. BSS(Business Support System)         -It handles the customer facing operations.
                                        -It includes:- Billing, Customer Relationship Management(CRM),
                                                       Order Management, Product Catalog Management.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. OSS(Operations Support System)        -It handles network facing operations.
                                         -It includes:- Network configurations, Services activation,
                                                        Monitoring the networking components
                                                        and Fault management.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Core Network                          -The central part of telecom the route call and data.
                                         -It includes:- MSC(Mobile Switching Center),
                                                        HLR(Home Location Register),
                                                        VLR(Visitor Location Register),
                                                        PCRF(Policy and Charging Rules Function)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Radio Access Network(RAN)            -It connects the end user devices through the network.
                                         -It includes:- Base Stations, Cell Towers,
                                                        Antennas, Radio Controllers.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. Value Added Services(VAS)            -It provides extra services.:- SMS(Short Message Service)
                                                                       MMS(Multimedia Messaging Service),
                                                                       Mobile TV, Music Streaming,
                                                                       Mobile Banking, Culler tune.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. 5G,4G,VoLTE,IoT                      -These are the latest technologies enabling faster, smarter and the communication.
                                            -5G and 4G are the mobile network technologies.
                                            -VoLTE(Voice over LTE) enables high quality voice calls.
                                            -IoT(Internet of Things) connects devices and systems for data exchange.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

