'''

#Networking Layers in Telecom Domain:-
'''
= Networking layers are created known as OSI layers(Open Systems Interconnection).

= Understanding OSI layers is important for anyone in telecom, networking, QA, or backend development,
  because every call, message, or data packet travel through OSI seven layers.
'''

#OSI Model Overview:-
'''
= The OSI model(developed by ISO) describes how data is moves from one system(computer or mobile) to another system
  over a network, in seven logical layers.
'''

#Seven Logical Layers of OSI Model:-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Layer Number          Layer Name               Function/Description                        Protocol/Device Example
------------         -----------              --------------------                        -----------------------
No.1✅             -Physical layer          -It transmission of bits                   -Cables, Hubs, fiber optics
                                             over the media(physical devices).          coper wires, wi-fi.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
No.2✅             -Data Link layer         -It handles physical addressing,            -Ethernet, Switches, PPP(Point to Point Protocol)
                                             error detection and correction.             PPP is one type of fault detection device.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
No.3✅             -Network layer           -It handles logical addressing(Connection), -IP(Internet Protocol), Routers
                                             routing(data transmission).                 ICMP(Internet Control Message Protocol)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
No.4✅             -Transport layer         -It ensures reliable data transfer          -TCP(Transmission Control Protocol),
                                             between end to end systems.                 UDP(User Datagram Protocol)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
No.5               -Session layer           -It manages sessions and connections         -NetBIOS, RPC(Remote Procedure Call)
                                             between applications.                        SIP(Session Initiation Protocol)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
No.6               -Presentation layer      -It handles data formatting,                -SSL(Secure Sockets Layer),
                                             encryption and compression.                 TLS(Transport Layer Security)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
No.7✅             -Application layer       -It provides User interface                -HTTP(Hypertext Transfer Protocol), DNS(Domain Name System)
                                             and network services                       FTP(File Transfer Protocol),
                                             to end user applications.                  SMTP(Simple Mail Transfer Protocol)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

