'''

#Telecom Business Architecture:-
'''
= In telecom companies, the entire system is mainly divided into three components:-

layer             Name                Purpose               Who Uses It
-----           ---------           ------------          --------------
1. Frontend     -CRM(Customer       -Handel the           -Call center employees,
                 Relationship        customer              Sales team
                 Management)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Middleware   -BSS(Business       -Handles the          -Billing payments,
                 Support System)     business              Customer data
                                     activities
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Backend     -OSS(Operations      -Handles the           -Network engineers,
                  Support System)    network                Service activation team
                                     operations
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
'''

#Telecom CRM(Customer Relationship Management):-
'''
= CRM is the system is used to interact with customers.

= Through CRM, Telecom employees can:-
  -Create a new customer profile(New sim card request).
  -Change customer plans.
  -Check complaints.
  -Track customer uses.
  -Generate service requests.
  -handle KYC(Know Your Customer) process.

= CRM Name Examples:-
  -Sibel CRM
  -Amdoc CRM
  -Salesforce CRM

#Example of CRM Use Case:-
-When you visit any telecom operator store to buy a new sim card,
 The executive team uses CRM to enter your details and create a account for you.

-If you are a existing customer and your pack is invalid for recharge a valid pack
 based on the end user request or third party request they can change the plan using CRM,
 The plans are:- Calls, SMS, Data(Internet), MMS, VOIP.
'''

#Telecom BSS(Business Support System):-
'''
= BSS manages all the business related activities of telecom operations.

= BSS is responsible for:-
  -Customer account management.
  -Billing and invoicing.
  -Recharge, payments and balance checks.
  -Product catalog and pricing.
  -Order management.

Note:- BSS ensure that the company earns money properly from the services provided to customers.

= BSS Name Examples:-
  -Amdocs Billing
  -Oracle BRM(Billing and Revenue Management)
  -Ericsson BSCS(Business Support and Control System)

= Example of BSS Use Case:-
  -When you recharge some pack BSS decide what benefits you should get
   and deduct the balance correctly from your account.
'''

#Telecom OSS(Operations Support System):-
'''
= OSS is responsible for telecom operations.

= OSS is responsible for:-
  -Tower and network management.
  -Service activation(Internet, call, sms)
  -Fault detection and network monitoring.
  -sim activation and provisioning
  -Network performance analysis.

= OSS Name Examples:-
  -NetAct
  -TeMIP
  -OSS-RC
  -Nagios
  -Solarwinds

= Example of OSS Use Case:-
  -When your sim card is activated,
   OSS send configuration to network element(HLR, VLR, MSC, GMSC, BSC, BTS)
'''

#OSS Architecture:-
'''
User:- Telecom agent, Sales, telecom employee.
USER-----URL-----WEB_PORTAl-----CRM-----BILLING(BSS)(Invoice)-----MEDIATION
                                 |                               (Recording)
                                 |                               (Prepaid-OSC)
                                 |                               (Postpaid-CDR)
                              ORDERING(SQL-ORM)
                                 | |                                          |NETWORK LAYER
                                 | |         PROVISIONING         |-----------|(BSC, BTS, MSC, GMSC)
                                 | |              |     |         |           |(CISCO Layer)
                               INVENTORY----------|     |         |           |
                              (Wear HOUSE)              |         |           |
                               (DataBase)            Activation---|           |
'''                                                    (OSS)
#The user(Telecom agent, sales, employ) interact in web portal, then go to the CRM, then check the ordering,
 Then check the inventory(DB, AWS EC2) for data is available or not, if the data is available, ordering check in the billing,
 then it going to provisioning, then provisioning check the billing send for activation, then for activation it connect with
 Network layer(BSC, BTS, MSC, GMSC), Then mediation for data recording(For prepaid use OSC, for postpaid use CDR).

#Which OSS you used:- OSS-RC
#In OSS-RC, you use which product:- Nagos


#User or Operator:-
'''
= It is a telecom agent, sales, employee which use telecom servers for the customers.
'''

#Web portal layer:-
'''
= It is used by human(agent, sales, employee) who interact with
  the system through the web portal layer.

= This layer provide access to service life for CRM Billing and ordering.
'''

#CRM:-
'''
= CRM is Customer Relationship Management.

= CRM connected to the BSS(Billing) for customer information, synchronizations
  and ensuring the right customer data is used for invoicing.

= CRM is connected to ordering for customer order, for new services or modifications.
'''

#Billing:-
'''
= Billing is the part of BSS, who have access to handel payment gateway system,
  invoicing, monthly bill generation, quarterly bill generation and yearly bill generation.
'''

#Mediation:-
'''
= This connection is process and validate, we record from the network before passing them to the billing system
  and they can track both prepaid and postpaid services.

= Prepaid services stored in OSC(Online Charging System) and Postpaid stored in CDR(Call Details Record).
'''

#Odering:-
'''
= Ordering for to the check product is available or not.

= Once order is confirmed it connected with the inventory(wear house)
    and check the particular product is available or not.

= If the product is available ordering fetch the invoice form billing and confirm to provisioning system.
'''

#Provisioning:-
'''
= Provisioning mainly used for to the track the order and activate the services.

= Provisioning directly interact with the OSS layer,
  it sends data to activation, component for service activation in the network.

= Based on the provisioning information, inventory is automatically updated.
'''

#Activation:-
'''
= Activation is a directly networking system, it interact with management network element
  to activate and modify the service for the customers.
'''

#Network Layer(CISCO):-
'''
= Network layer used to, after activate the new services or modify the existing services.

= It is directly use the telecom physical products or elements(BSC, BTC, MSC, GMSC, HLR, VLR, SS7).
'''


