#Which section of telecom you first communicate through your any devices?
'''
= BTS(Base Transmission Station) is the first point of communication between your device and the telecom network.
= When you make a call or send a message, your device connects to the nearest BTS.
= The BTS then relays your communication to the core network for further processing and routing.
'''

#What is UIN in Telecom Domain?
'''
= UIN(Unique Identification Number).
= Your Mobile number.
'''

#What is ABIS Interface?
'''
= It is a redio network frequency.
= Example:- we use Internet use when we on the aeroplane over the air.
'''

#What is 'A interface'?
'''
= It is a type of communication protocol.
= It is used between BSC(Base Station Controller) and MSC(Mobile Switching Center).
= It help to transmit the digital signal.
= It is used for call setup, routing and management.
= It is part of the SS7(Signal System number 7) protocol suite.
'''

#What is subscriber id:- Your UIN(Mobile Number).

#How to know what is secret key(KI) of your sim card?
'''
= It is written like this:-
  -KI#0000 a7b411202i369
'''

#Draw the circuit diagram of End to End Voice Call Flow in Telecom Domain:-
'''
= User A(MS-A) -----> BTS-A -----> BSC-A -----> MSC-A -----> GMSC-B -----> MSC-B -----> BSC-B -----> BTS-B -----> User B(MS-B)
'''

#MS-A(Mobile Station A) Connect to BTS(Base Transmission/Transceiver Station) through SS7(Signal System number7),
 BTS connect with BSC(Base Station Controller), BSC connect with MSC(Mobile Switching Center)

#Which type of voice is coming from MS-A:- Analog voice, Analog voice coming to the receiver,
 Then receiver transmit the voice, then convert into digital signal.

